  "prompt": "How to connect with Bluetooth headset in Android?",
  "response": "Here's a step-by-step guide to connect a Bluetooth headset to an Android device:\n\n1. Enable Bluetooth\n- Go to Settings\n- Tap on \"Connections\" or \"Bluetooth\"\n- Toggle Bluetooth on\n\n2. Put Headset in Pairing Mode\n- Turn on your Bluetooth headset\n- Press and hold the pairing button (usually for 3-5 seconds)\n- Look for a blinking light or hear a pairing sound\n\n3. Pair the Devices\n- On your Android phone, tap \"Pair new device\"\n- Your headset should appear in the list of available devices\n- Tap on the headset's name\n- If prompted, enter pairing code (often 0000 or 1234)\n\n4. Complete Connection\n- Wait for the devices to pair\n- Once connected, you'll see a confirmation message\n\nTroubleshooting Tips:\n- Ensure headset is charged\n- Keep devices close during pairing\n- Restart both devices if pairing fails\n- Update Android system and device software\n- Remove previous Bluetooth pairings if needed\n\nNote: Exact steps might vary slightly depending on your Android version and device model.",
